            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "If you take a closer look at the documentation, you will notice that the static_path parameter you're referring to is for the URL path, not the local filesystem path.  To quote the docs, \"This does not affect the folder the files are served from.\"\n\nAs for the template directory, yes, it is possible to do, but no, it is not easy or obvious.  Especially when Flask \"modules\" are in use.\n"
